{
  "text": "After we identified the establishment year of rubber plantations, we tracked pre-conversion land cover by analyzing the time-series vegetation indices. The conversion of grassland to rubber plantations was limited because grassland accounts for only 3.3% of the total land area [CITATION_1] , and the conversion of water and built-up areas to rubber plantations were highly unlikely, so our study focused on the conversion of evergreen forests, old rubber plantations, and cropland to rubber plantations. First, we identified the pre-conversion land cover as cropland or forest by observing LSWIleafon_min of Nx years before plantation was established. A cropland usually has some observations with LSWIleafon_min < 0 in a year due to exposed soils after harvest and during the fallow period. Here ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15750492"
